text: Porton Barracks was founded in 1971 as the home of the 51st Battalion, Far North Queensland Regiment. Porton Barracks was named after the Battle of Porton Plantation. A battle during the Second World War that involved the 31st/51st Battalion, Royal Queensland Regiment. == Current units == * 51st Battalion, Far North Queensland Regiment * Delta Company, 31st/42nd Battalion, Royal Queensland Regiment *134 ACU (Army Cadet Unit) ==References== Category:Barracks in Australia Category:Military installations in Queensland Category:Buildings and structures in Cairns
title: Porton Barracks
